## Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Brother's Fashion Zone Next.js project.

### Changes Made

1. **Package Installation**
   - Installed `@vercel/speed-insights@^2.0.0` via npm
   - Package added to dependencies in package.json
   - package-lock.json updated with new dependency tree

2. **Integration into Root Layout**
   - Modified: `src/app/layout.tsx`
   - Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/next'`
   - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component within the `<body>` tag, after the ScrollToTop component
   - Component placement ensures it's loaded on all pages across the application

3. **Framework Configuration**
   - Project uses Next.js App Router (v16.2.5)
   - Used the official Next.js App Router integration (`@vercel/speed-insights/next`)
   - Component correctly placed in the root layout for global coverage

### Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel Speed Insights documentation fetched from:
https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart

The SpeedInsights component was added to the root layout file at `src/app/layout.tsx`, which ensures that Speed Insights will track performance metrics across all pages in the application. The component is positioned after other layout components to avoid interfering with the page's critical rendering path.

### Verification Steps Completed

1. ✅ Fetched latest documentation from Vercel
2. ✅ Identified framework (Next.js App Router)
3. ✅ Installed package using npm (project's package manager)
4. ✅ Added SpeedInsights component to root layout
5. ✅ Ran linter - no new errors introduced (0 errors, 93 pre-existing warnings)
6. ✅ Preserved existing code structure and formatting
7. ✅ Updated lock files (package-lock.json)

### Post-Deployment Steps

After deploying this change to Vercel:
1. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel project dashboard
2. Monitor performance data collection after user visits
3. View metrics in the Vercel Speed Insights dashboard

### Notes

- The build process has a pre-existing issue related to missing Supabase configuration (supabaseUrl), unrelated to this implementation
- All changes follow the existing code patterns and TypeScript conventions in the project
- The component is placed within the CartProvider context, after all other UI components
